hpicfIpSla.name: hpicfIpSla

revisions.description: Changed the MIB description of PayloadSize
Added MIB objects for UDP, TCP and ICMP show functions
Added MIB objects for DNS and DHCP error counts.
Added MIB object for status and next schedule value.
Removed Added codec type and advantage factor.

hpicfIpSla.contactinfo: Hewlett Packard Enterprise Development LP. 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfIpSla.description: This MIB module contains HP proprietary objects for managing IP Service Level Agreement (SLA).

hpicfIpSlaTable.name: hpicfIpSlaTable
hpicfIpSlaTable.description: This table specifies IP SLA test parameters as SLA entries.

hpicfIpSlaEntry.name: hpicfIpSlaEntry
hpicfIpSlaEntry.description: An entry on this table specifies the destination IP address/ Hostname, Source address, Source Interface ID & Row status corresponding to each SLA test.

hpicfIpSlaID.name: hpicfIpSlaID
hpicfIpSlaID.description: This is an identifier for the IP SLA.

hpicfIpSlaType.name: hpicfIpSlaType
hpicfIpSlaType.description: SLA Probe Type. IcmpEcho is similar to ping protocol and the destination should be enabled with responder functionality for udpEcho, udpJitter, udpJitterVoIP and tcpConnect. For DHCP and DNS, destination device should be enabled with DHCP and DNS servers, respectively.

hpicfIpSlaAdminState.name: hpicfIpSlaAdminState
hpicfIpSlaAdminState.description: Enable or disable the IP Service Level Agreement (SLA) probe.

hpicfIpSlaL4SourcePort.name: hpicfIpSlaL4SourcePort
hpicfIpSlaL4SourcePort.description: SLA source port to be used for SLA probes that use a transport layer such as udpEcho, udpJitter, udpJitterVoIP and tcpConnect. The allowed range is from 1024 to 65535.

hpicfIpSlaL4DestPort.name: hpicfIpSlaL4DestPort
hpicfIpSlaL4DestPort.description: Port on target device which responds back to the probe. This is used for SLA probes that use a transport layer such as udpEcho, udpJitter, udpJitterVoIP and tcpConnect SLA types. The allowed range is from 1024 to 65535.

hpicfIpSlaAttrTable.name: hpicfIpSlaAttrTable
hpicfIpSlaAttrTable.description: This table specifies IP SLA test parameters as SLA entries.

hpicfIpSlaAttrEntry.name: hpicfIpSlaAttrEntry
hpicfIpSlaAttrEntry.description: An entry on this table specifies the attributes of SLA test such as scheduling parameters, TOS, payload size, history bucket size and inter packet interval, corresponding to each SLA test.

hpicfIpSlaSchedStartTime.name: hpicfIpSlaSchedStartTime
hpicfIpSlaSchedStartTime.description: Timestamp to denote when to start this SLA probe.

hpicfIpSlaSchedEndTime.name: hpicfIpSlaSchedEndTime
hpicfIpSlaSchedEndTime.description: Timestamp to denote when to end this SLA probe.

hpicfIpSlaSchedFreq.name: hpicfIpSlaSchedFreq
hpicfIpSlaSchedFreq.description: Frequency in seconds. This value is used to send probes.

hpicfIpSlaSchedRepeat.name: hpicfIpSlaSchedRepeat
hpicfIpSlaSchedRepeat.description: Number of times this test will be repeated.

hpicfIpSlaAttrTOS.name: hpicfIpSlaAttrTOS
hpicfIpSlaAttrTOS.description: Type of service value to be set for the probe packet.

hpicfIpSlaAttrHistorySize.name: hpicfIpSlaAttrHistorySize
hpicfIpSlaAttrHistorySize.description: Number of history records to be maintained for SLA test. Size can vary from 1 to 50.

hpicfIpSlaAttrPayloadSize.name: hpicfIpSlaAttrPayloadSize
hpicfIpSlaAttrPayloadSize.description: Size of the packet payload to be sent out for each probe. It can be set from 0 to 1440 for udpEcho, icmpEcho and from 68 to 8100 for udpJitter.

hpicfIpSlaAttrNumPkts.name: hpicfIpSlaAttrNumPkts
hpicfIpSlaAttrNumPkts.description: Number of packets to be sent out for a single probe for jitter SLA type.

hpicfIpSlaAttrPktInterval.name: hpicfIpSlaAttrPktInterval
hpicfIpSlaAttrPktInterval.description: Inter packet interval in milli seconds. Which is to be used for packets that are sent out for a single probe for jitter SLA type.

hpicfIpSlaAttrCodecType.name: hpicfIpSlaAttrCodecType
hpicfIpSlaAttrCodecType.description: Codec-type for the VoIP SLA test.

hpicfIpSlaAttrAdvntgFactr.name: hpicfIpSlaAttrAdvntgFactr
hpicfIpSlaAttrAdvntgFactr.description: Advantage factor to calculate the MOS and ICPIF values for VoIP SLA type.

hpicfIpSlaThrTable.name: hpicfIpSlaThrTable
hpicfIpSlaThrTable.description: This table specifies IP SLA threshold-action parameters as entries. When one of the monitored parameters of an SLA test goes beyond the configured thresholds, notifications are generated either as traps or syslog messages.

hpicfIpSlaThrEntry.name: hpicfIpSlaThrEntry
hpicfIpSlaThrEntry.description: An entry on this table specifies the Metric type, upper and lower limit of thresholds, threshold type and action to be taken.

hpicfIpSlaThrMetricType.name: hpicfIpSlaThrMetricType
hpicfIpSlaThrMetricType.description: SLA metric type to be monitored. The rtt type is the round trip time of the probe packet. The jitter type is the inter-packet delay variance. The srcTodstTime type is the one-way trip time from source to destination. The dstTosrcTtime type is the one-way trip time from destination to source. The Mean Opinion Scores (MOS) type is derived only for udpJitterVoIP SLA. The Calculated Planning Impairment Factor (ICPIF) type is derived only for udpJitterVoIP SLA. ThepacketLoss type is to monitor loss of communication. The testCompletion type is for notifying about the completion of probe test. The sdJitterPos type is the source-to-destination positive jitter and the dsJitterPos type is the destination-to-source positivejitter.

hpicfIpSlaThrUpper.name: hpicfIpSlaThrUpper
hpicfIpSlaThrUpper.description: Acceptable upper-limit of threshold value for SLA. This value is not applicable when hpicfIpSlaThrMetricType is set to packetLoss and testCompletion.

hpicfIpSlaThrLower.name: hpicfIpSlaThrLower
hpicfIpSlaThrLower.description: Acceptable lower-limit of threshold value for SLA. This value is not applicable when hpicfIpSlaThrMetricType is set to packetLoss and testCompletion.

hpicfIpSlaThrType.name: hpicfIpSlaThrType
hpicfIpSlaThrType.description: Configure threshold type to trigger action. When a trap/log has to be generated each time the threshold is breached, immediate threshold type can be used. The Consecutive threshold type generates traps/logs when the threshold is violated a certain number of times This value is not applicable when hpicfIpSlaThrMetricType is set to testCompletion. The aggregated threshold type is used to generate traps/logs for aggregated probes.

hpicfIpSlaThrCount.name: hpicfIpSlaThrCount
hpicfIpSlaThrCount.description: The value for the number of consecutive times the upper or lower limit of the threshold is violated. For example, this can be configured to trigger a trap/log when the RTT is more than the upper limit, x number of times consecutively. This value is applicable only if hpicfIpSlaThrType is set to consecutive.

hpicfIpSlaThrAction.name: hpicfIpSlaThrAction
hpicfIpSlaThrAction.description: The number of probe packets used to calculate Round Trip Time for jitter test.

hpicfIpSlaRespTable.name: hpicfIpSlaRespTable
hpicfIpSlaRespTable.description: This table specifies IP SLA responder parameters as entries.

hpicfIpSlaRespEntry.name: hpicfIpSlaRespEntry
hpicfIpSlaRespEntry.description: An entry on this table specifies the local IP address, port number and row status corresponding to each SLA responder config.

hpicfIpSlaRespType.name: hpicfIpSlaRespType
hpicfIpSlaRespType.description: The SLA responder type. The udpEcho and tcpConnect objects are for UDP and TCP packets, respectively. The udpJitter and udpJitterVoIP values calculate one-way delay, therefore a timestamp has to be embedded while replying back. This is one of the indexes for the hpicfIpSlaRespTable.

hpicfIpSlaRespAddress.name: hpicfIpSlaRespAddress
hpicfIpSlaRespAddress.description: The local IP address to which the responder is bound. This is one of the indexes for the hpicfIpSlaRespTable.

hpicfIpSlaRespL4Port.name: hpicfIpSlaRespL4Port
hpicfIpSlaRespL4Port.description: L4 port number on hpicfIpSlaRespAddress where the responder listens for probe packets from SLA source. This is one of the indexes for the hpicfIpSlaRespTable. The allowed range is from 1024 to 65535.

hpicfIpSlaRespResultTable.name: hpicfIpSlaRespResultTable
hpicfIpSlaRespResultTable.description: This table specifies the IP SLA responder result parameters as entries.

hpicfIpSlaRespResultEntry.name: hpicfIpSlaRespResultEntry
hpicfIpSlaRespResultEntry.description: An entry on this table specifies responder status and number of packets received and responded.

hpicfIpSlaRespnumPktRcvd.name: hpicfIpSlaRespnumPktRcvd
hpicfIpSlaRespnumPktRcvd.description: The number of packets received by the responder.

hpicfIpSlaRespNumPktRespnd.name: hpicfIpSlaRespNumPktRespnd
hpicfIpSlaRespNumPktRespnd.description: The number of packets sent by the responder.

hpicfIpSlaJitterRespTable.name: hpicfIpSlaJitterRespTable
hpicfIpSlaJitterRespTable.description: This table specifies IP SLA jitter responder parameters as entries.

hpicfIpSlaJitterRespEntry.name: hpicfIpSlaJitterRespEntry
hpicfIpSlaJitterRespEntry.description: An entry on this table specifies the local IP address, port number and row status corresponding to each SLA responder config.

hpicfIpSlaJitterRespType.name: hpicfIpSlaJitterRespType
hpicfIpSlaJitterRespType.description: The SLA jitter responder type. The udpJitter and udpJitterVoIP values calculate one-way delay, therefore a timestamp has to be embedded while replying back. This is one of the indexes for hpicfIpSlaJitterRespTable.

hpicfIpSlaJitterRespAddressType.name: hpicfIpSlaJitterRespAddressType
hpicfIpSlaJitterRespAddressType.description: SLA jitter responder IP address type.

hpicfIpSlaJitterRespAddress.name: hpicfIpSlaJitterRespAddress
hpicfIpSlaJitterRespAddress.description: The local IP address to which the responder is bound. This is one of the indexes for hpicfIpSlaJitterRespTable.

hpicfIpSlaJitterRespL4Port.name: hpicfIpSlaJitterRespL4Port
hpicfIpSlaJitterRespL4Port.description: L4 port number on hpicfIpSlaJitterRespAddress where the responder listens for probe packets from SLA source. This is one of the indexes for hpicfIpSlaJitterRespTable. The allowed range is 1024 to 65535.

hpicfIpSlaJitterRespSrcAddrType.name: hpicfIpSlaJitterRespSrcAddrType
hpicfIpSlaJitterRespSrcAddrType.description: SLA jitter responder source IP address type.

hpicfIpSlaJitterRespSrcAddress.name: hpicfIpSlaJitterRespSrcAddress
hpicfIpSlaJitterRespSrcAddress.description: The source IP address to which the responder is responding.

hpicfIpSlaThresholdexceeded.name: hpicfIpSlaThresholdexceeded
hpicfIpSlaThresholdexceeded.description: This notification is generated when the metric calculated from the SLA result exceeds the configured threshold value. The hpicfIpSlaThrUpper is not applicable when hpicfIpSlaThrMetricType is set to packetLoss or testCompletion.

hpicfIpSlaTestCompletion.name: hpicfIpSlaTestCompletion
hpicfIpSlaTestCompletion.description: This notification is generated when the SLA test is completed either by reaching stopTime or hpicfIpSlaAttrNumPkts. This notification is sent only when the action type is set to trap or trap-log.

hpicfIpSlaThresholdPktLoss.name: hpicfIpSlaThresholdPktLoss
hpicfIpSlaThresholdPktLoss.description: This notification is generated when SLA test probe reply packets are lost consecutively for the configured number of hpicfIpSlaThrCount. This notification is sent only when the action type is set to trap or trap-log.
